	DC.B	"                               About Myself                                     "
	DC.B	"                              --------------                                    "
	DC.B	"                                                                                "
	DC.B	"  Oh well, how on Earth am I supposed to introduce myself?  I doubt if you      "
	DC.B	"have ever heard of me if you are not one of the regular contributers to         "
	DC.B	"ACC, the totally cool coding magazine edited by Mark Meany.                     "
	DC.B	"  I am a 17 years old lad, and have been messing around with computers          "
	DC.B	"since about 1982, when I got the good ol' ZX Spectrum 48k. I had this for       "
	DC.B	"about 4 years, and then had a minor brain failure and bought an Atari 520       "
	DC.B	"STFM...  Oh shit, I thought, what a fucking shite computer...                   "
	DC.B	"Unfortuanately, I didn't realise this until two years after I bought it...      "
	DC.B	"I sold the shit bucket for 200 quid (great price!) and raised another 100       "
	DC.B	"by selling my very small collection of (original) games. I got the other        "
	DC.B	"100 from elsewhere and bought myself an A500, just before the ECS was           "
	DC.B	"fitted as standard. Bastard...                                                  "
	DC.B	"                                                                                "
	DC.B	"  I soon bought the memory upgrade and a Cumana external drive, coz I           "
	DC.B	"wanted to learn how to code!  The first demo I saw was the RSI megademo and     "
	DC.B	"I just wanted to know how to do it...                                           "
	DC.B	"                                                                                "
	DC.B	"   It's nearly two years on and I still don't have a fucking clue... :-)        "
	DC.B	"                                                                                "
	DC.B	"                                                      Master Beat               "
